---
title: Color palette theme variables
---

A simple, single series, bar chart mainly for testing the application of the plotting color palette (`--plot-color-1`, `--plot-color-2`, ...) across plotting libraries.

# Python

Plots generated in Python using Matplotlib, Plotly Express, and Altair.

```python exec
import pandas as pd

df = pd.DataFrame({
    'x': ['A', 'B', 'C', 'D', 'E', 'F', 'G', 'H', 'I', 'J', 'K', 'L'],
    'y': list(range(1, 13))
})
```

## matplotlib

```python exec
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

bars = plt.bar(df['x'], df['y'], color=[f'C{i}' for i in range(12)])
plt.xlabel('x')
plt.ylabel('y')
plt.legend(bars, df['x'], loc=plt.rcParams["legend.loc"])
```

## Seaborn

```python exec
import seaborn as sns

ax = sns.barplot(data=df, x='x', y='y', hue='x', legend='full')
sns.move_legend(ax, loc=plt.rcParams["legend.loc"])
ax
```

## Plotly

```python exec
import plotly.express as px

px.bar(df, x='x', y='y', color='x')
```

## Altair

```python exec
import altair as alt

alt.Chart(df).mark_bar().encode(x='x', y='y', color='x')
```

# R

Plots generated in R using base plotting and `ggplot2`.

## Base plotting

```r exec
barplot(1:12, names.arg = LETTERS[1:12], xlab = "x", ylab = "y", col = 1:12, legend.text = LETTERS[1:12], args.legend = list(x = "topright", inset = c(-0.15, 0), xpd = TRUE))
```

## ggplot

```r exec
library(ggplot2)

ggplot(data.frame(x = factor(LETTERS[1:12]), y = 1:12), aes(x = x, y = y, fill = x)) + geom_col()
```

